Clarity 6 (SIP-04x): allow identifiers to begin with `_` (e.g. `_admin`, `_-internal`) for `define-*` names, function arguments, and `let`/`match` bindings. Additionally, the bare identifier `_` is a discard pattern in `let` and `match` bindings — its value is evaluated (preserving short-circuit effects of `try!`/`unwrap!`) but no binding is added to scope, and repeated `_` bindings in the same form do not conflict. Gated on `ClarityVersion::Clarity6`; pre-Clarity-6 contracts continue to reject leading-`_` identifiers at parse time.
